00:13:41.585 --> 00:13:45.005
Stranger Things are, in some ways, simply

00:13:45.095 --> 00:13:48.015
developments, and certainly more expensive

00:13:48.055 --> 00:13:50.485
developments, on the Penny Dreadful genre.

00:13:51.915 --> 00:13:54.655
And the serialised format certainly

00:13:54.655 --> 00:13:56.515
helped boost their popularity.

00:13:57.435 --> 00:14:00.015
Just like if your favourite TV series

00:14:00.115 --> 00:14:02.685
ends on a cliffhanger, ends with something

00:14:02.795 --> 00:14:04.575
exciting happening that might change

00:14:04.575 --> 00:14:07.415
the plot completely, well this was

00:14:07.415 --> 00:14:09.575
exactly the same with the Penny Dreadful.

00:14:10.715 --> 00:14:12.845
People would save their money, eagerly

00:14:12.875 --> 00:14:15.025
awaiting the next instalment so they

00:14:15.025 --> 00:14:16.665
could see what would happen next.

00:14:17.905 --> 00:14:20.485
There were even stories of book clubs

00:14:20.625 --> 00:14:23.265
being formed, kids who couldn’t afford

00:14:23.275 --> 00:14:25.515
the 1 penny price tag would club

00:14:25.515 --> 00:14:28.525
together and buy a book to share, and

00:14:28.685 --> 00:14:30.465
even those children who weren’t able

00:14:30.465 --> 00:14:33.265
to read would join the club and listen

00:14:33.455 --> 00:14:35.435
to the story being read out loud.

00:14:36.515 --> 00:14:38.915
Initially, the subjects tended to be

00:14:39.195 --> 00:14:42.095
believable but “real-life” style stories

00:14:42.445 --> 00:14:46.125
- murderers, adventure, and so on, but all

00:14:46.135 --> 00:14:48.745
within the confines of the “real” world.

00:14:50.005 --> 00:14:51.915
As time went on, Penny

00:14:51.915 --> 00:14:54.455
Dreadfuls started to become more

00:14:54.485 --> 00:14:56.445
supernatural as well, involving

00:14:56.735 --> 00:14:59.135
supernatural beasts and goings-on.

00:14:59.858 --> 00:15:02.738
There were vampires, ghosts, evil

00:15:02.738 --> 00:15:05.982
spirits, all of whom would commit gruesome

00:15:06.002 --> 00:15:08.502
crimes to the delight of their readers.

00:15:09.792 --> 00:15:13.332
But, as with any new craze, especially

00:15:13.332 --> 00:15:16.472
one that captivates the hearts and minds

00:15:16.492 --> 00:15:19.142
of the young, it wasn’t long before there

00:15:19.142 --> 00:15:21.572
were as many critics as there were fans.

00:15:23.112 --> 00:15:25.742
Much like horror movies or violent

00:15:25.742 --> 00:15:27.572
video games today, there were

00:15:27.622 --> 00:15:30.072
adult critics who feared the impact

00:15:30.222 --> 00:15:32.072
that devouring these stories would

00:15:32.082 --> 00:15:34.042
have on the children of the time.

00:15:35.403 --> 00:15:37.972
Victorians were famously moralistic,

00:15:38.172 --> 00:15:40.512
with the upper classes feeling like

00:15:40.512 --> 00:15:42.928
they had a moral duty to protect

00:15:42.968 --> 00:15:46.118
their supposed inferiors from moral

00:15:46.118 --> 00:15:48.508
decay, and the phenomenon of the

00:15:48.538 --> 00:15:50.468
Penny Dreadful was really the first

00:15:50.478 --> 00:15:53.508
time that society en masse had had

00:15:53.538 --> 00:15:55.678
access to this kind of entertainment.

00:15:56.998 --> 00:15:59.888
It’s hard to overstate the fear and

00:15:59.888 --> 00:16:02.258
moral panic that ensued, with one

00:16:02.268 --> 00:16:05.598
newspaper in 1886 even declaring

00:16:05.768 --> 00:16:08.158
that penny dreadfuls were, I quote,

00:16:08.538 --> 00:16:10.628
“the poison which is threatening to

00:16:10.628 --> 00:16:13.218
destroy the manhood of democracy”.

00:16:14.550 --> 00:16:14.817
Why?

00:16:15.587 --> 00:16:18.298
Well, just like video games, people

00:16:18.298 --> 00:16:21.348
feared that simply reading about crime

00:16:21.538 --> 00:16:23.658
would mean that someone was more likely

00:16:23.658 --> 00:16:26.148
to commit crimes, that reading violent

00:16:26.158 --> 00:16:29.018
stories could inspire violent acts.

00:16:29.958 --> 00:16:32.738
And in the final two decades of the 19th

00:16:32.768 --> 00:16:35.068
century, after the penny dreadful craze

00:16:35.068 --> 00:16:37.508
had reached its height, people were

00:16:37.518 --> 00:16:39.928
increasingly blaming the stories for

00:16:39.928 --> 00:16:42.438
crimes actually committed by children.

00:16:43.588 --> 00:16:45.378
Almost every month, there would be

00:16:45.568 --> 00:16:48.548
news stories of crimes or acts that

00:16:48.548 --> 00:16:50.258
were blamed on Penny Dreadfuls.

00:16:51.758 --> 00:16:54.458
In 1892 there was one of some

00:16:54.598 --> 00:16:57.548
schoolboys who ran away with a gun and

00:16:57.548 --> 00:16:59.358
were caught with a note which read:

00:17:00.058 --> 00:17:01.538
“Steal the money; go to the

00:17:01.538 --> 00:17:02.998
station and get to Glasgow.

00:17:03.368 --> 00:17:04.828
Get boat for America”.

00:17:06.198 --> 00:17:08.568
People believed the boys were inspired

00:17:08.588 --> 00:17:10.878
by tales such as Jack Harkaway’s

00:17:11.208 --> 00:17:13.408
Schooldays, which was about a boy who

00:17:13.408 --> 00:17:15.618
ran away to begin a life of adventure.

00:17:16.948 --> 00:17:19.378
In the same year, the suicide of a

00:17:19.428 --> 00:17:21.868
12-year-old boy who hanged himself

00:17:21.968 --> 00:17:24.268
was also blamed on penny dreadfuls.

00:17:25.018 --> 00:17:27.408
In court, the verdict was announced

00:17:27.558 --> 00:17:30.708
as “suicide during temporary insanity,

00:17:31.028 --> 00:17:33.708
induced by reading trashy novels”.

00:17:35.268 --> 00:17:38.198
But tensions really hit an all-time

00:17:38.218 --> 00:17:41.558
high in 1895, when the body of a

00:17:41.558 --> 00:17:43.888
woman was found in a house in London.

00:17:45.018 --> 00:17:46.918
The police didn’t have to search far

00:17:47.048 --> 00:17:49.408
for her killers, as they were, in

00:17:49.408 --> 00:17:52.568
fact, her 12- and 13-year-old sons.

00:17:53.728 --> 00:17:55.758
The elder boy had insisted that

00:17:55.798 --> 00:17:57.638
his brother told him to stab their

00:17:57.638 --> 00:18:00.058
mother to death, and when the police

00:18:00.088 --> 00:18:02.958
investigated, they found a huge collection

00:18:03.148 --> 00:18:05.088
of penny dreadfuls in the house.

00:18:06.288 --> 00:18:08.428
The copies were used as evidence in

00:18:08.428 --> 00:18:11.438
the case and in court a judge called

00:18:11.438 --> 00:18:14.378
for laws to “stop the inflammable and

00:18:14.378 --> 00:18:16.308
shocking literature that is sold.”

00:18:17.898 --> 00:18:20.018
All of these controversies were the

00:18:20.018 --> 00:18:22.148
beginning of the end for the penny

00:18:22.148 --> 00:18:25.018
dreadful craze, as publishers began to

00:18:25.028 --> 00:18:27.368
distance themselves from problematic

00:18:27.368 --> 00:18:29.648
material and real-life tragedies.

00:18:30.258 --> 00:18:32.208
It’s not exactly good for business

00:18:32.248 --> 00:18:33.998
if you’re being blamed for causing

00:18:33.998 --> 00:18:35.848
terrible murders and suicides.

00:18:37.118 --> 00:18:39.608
As a result, there was a gap in the

00:18:39.608 --> 00:18:42.318
market for more uplifting stories for

00:18:42.318 --> 00:18:45.401
children, stories that included moral

00:18:45.401 --> 00:18:48.148
or educational lessons, stories that

00:18:48.378 --> 00:18:50.638
ended well, stories without murder,

00:18:50.968 --> 00:18:53.398
violence or brutality, stories that

00:18:53.418 --> 00:18:55.728
a parent would be much happier to buy

00:18:55.738 --> 00:18:57.618
for their child than a Penny Dreadful.

00:18:58.718 --> 00:19:01.048
The patriotically named The Union

00:19:01.048 --> 00:19:03.908
Jack was one of them, and in fact the

00:19:03.908 --> 00:19:06.448
entire objective of The Union Jack

00:19:06.608 --> 00:19:10.068
was, and I’m quoting directly, to “put

00:19:10.258 --> 00:19:12.268
the Penny Dreadfuls out of business”.

00:19:13.348 --> 00:19:15.238
The Union Jack had another

00:19:15.318 --> 00:19:17.458
large advantage - its price.

00:19:18.288 --> 00:19:20.898
It cost half a penny, half as

00:19:20.898 --> 00:19:22.648
much money as a Penny Dreadful.

00:19:23.948 --> 00:19:25.958
For a budget-conscious audience,

00:19:26.318 --> 00:19:28.838
clearly this was a big advantage.

00:19:30.078 --> 00:19:32.258
What’s more, there was a shift away

00:19:32.258 --> 00:19:34.718
from serialised-fiction towards

00:19:34.858 --> 00:19:37.118
full-length books, so when you could

00:19:37.128 --> 00:19:39.778
buy a full novel of a few hundred

00:19:39.778 --> 00:19:42.358
pages for the price of a handful of

00:19:42.358 --> 00:19:44.654
Penny Dreadfuls, and the quality of the

00:19:44.744 --> 00:19:47.429
narrative was a lot better, this option

00:19:47.619 --> 00:19:49.659
suddenly wasn’t so expensive at all.

00:19:51.069 --> 00:19:53.299
And on the other end of the spectrum,

00:19:53.699 --> 00:19:56.866
during the 1870s there was a boom in

00:19:56.906 --> 00:19:59.476
comic books, illustrated books, Which

00:19:59.476 --> 00:20:01.606
were even more accessible than penny

00:20:01.606 --> 00:20:03.796
dreadfuls, because there were pictures.

00:20:05.146 --> 00:20:06.936
The Penny Dreadful genre was

00:20:07.096 --> 00:20:09.256
being squeezed from all sides.

00:20:09.736 --> 00:20:11.966
Everything that had made it so popular

00:20:12.386 --> 00:20:15.946
- its price, its accessibility, its blood

00:20:16.266 --> 00:20:19.176
and gore - was now available in different

00:20:19.186 --> 00:20:22.236
formats, formats that were often preferred

00:20:22.256 --> 00:20:24.296
by readers that had once snapped up

00:20:24.556 --> 00:20:26.386
every Penny Dreadful on the shelf.

00:20:27.606 --> 00:20:29.609
By the turn of the century, the Penny

00:20:29.609 --> 00:20:31.889
Dreadful had practically died out.

00:20:33.229 --> 00:20:36.259
Now, when it comes to the legacy of the

00:20:36.269 --> 00:20:38.909
Penny Dreadful, fortunately the fears

00:20:38.909 --> 00:20:41.509
about the genre destroying all morality

00:20:41.509 --> 00:20:44.279
and poisoning democracy didn't come true.

00:20:45.371 --> 00:20:47.351
Perhaps they might have inspired

00:20:47.641 --> 00:20:50.951
some reckless behaviour, even violent

00:20:50.951 --> 00:20:53.331
acts, but did they turn an entire

00:20:53.331 --> 00:20:56.411
generation into rampant serial killers?

00:20:57.161 --> 00:20:57.681
They did not.

00:20:58.701 --> 00:21:02.141
In fact, many commentators now point to

00:21:02.141 --> 00:21:04.391
the positive impact of the Penny Dreadful.

00:21:05.421 --> 00:21:08.081
Sure, they may not have had the literary

00:21:08.081 --> 00:21:10.781
merit of Jane Austen, Charles Dickens,

00:21:10.781 --> 00:21:13.741
or Shakespeare, but they did encourage a

00:21:13.781 --> 00:21:16.111
generation of children to start reading.

00:21:17.531 --> 00:21:19.911
As one professor put it, penny

00:21:19.911 --> 00:21:21.931
dreadfuls gave children “an

00:21:21.931 --> 00:21:24.551
incentive to require literacy”.

00:21:25.176 --> 00:21:26.491
In other words, they gave

00:21:26.491 --> 00:21:28.501
children a reason, or some

00:21:28.581 --> 00:21:30.331
motivation to learn to read.

00:21:30.921 --> 00:21:33.311
They didn’t want to be left out when

00:21:33.341 --> 00:21:35.061
everyone else was talking about the

00:21:35.321 --> 00:21:38.171
latest robbery by Dick Turpin or who

00:21:38.371 --> 00:21:40.261
Sweeney Todd’s latest victim was.

00:21:41.621 --> 00:21:44.501
Now, it’s clearly an overstatement to say

00:21:44.501 --> 00:21:47.401
that the Penny Dreadfuls single-handedly

00:21:47.421 --> 00:21:49.281
increased literacy rates in Victorian

00:21:49.281 --> 00:21:51.641
Britain, as there were plenty of other

00:21:51.651 --> 00:21:54.011
factors that taught children how to read.

00:21:54.741 --> 00:21:57.771
But, the Penny Dreadfuls did inspire a

00:21:57.771 --> 00:22:00.911
generation to keep reading, to use the

00:22:00.911 --> 00:22:02.731
skills that they had learned at school.

00:22:03.741 --> 00:22:06.841
So, despite the critics and fears for the

00:22:06.841 --> 00:22:10.031
morality of Victorian youth, and fears

00:22:10.121 --> 00:22:11.861
that they would lead to the destruction of

00:22:11.861 --> 00:22:14.811
the very fabric of society, it certainly

00:22:14.811 --> 00:22:17.241
seems that there are many worse things

00:22:17.411 --> 00:22:19.971
a Victorian child could have done than

00:22:19.971 --> 00:22:22.068
getting addicted to Penny Dreadfuls.

00:22:24.641 --> 00:22:26.971
Ok then, that is it for today’s

00:22:26.981 --> 00:22:29.281
episode on Penny Dreadfuls.

00:22:29.571 --> 00:22:30.921
I hope it was an interesting one,

00:22:30.971 --> 00:22:32.621
and that you learned something new.

